Package stacks

Class Navigator

java.lang.Object
stacks.Navigator
public class Navigator
extends java.lang.Object
Define the class Navigator that provides three navigation options where the user can, set the current link via setCurrentLink(linkName) method, replace the current link by going back one link via goBack() method, and replace the current link by going forward one link via goForward() method.

  • Constructor Details

    • Navigator

      public Navigator()
      default constructor that takes no parameter. This constructor set everything into null since there is no link yet to be collected. Nothing will be printed.

    • Navigator

      public Navigator​(java.lang.String currentLink, StackList<java.lang.String> backLinks, StackList<java.lang.String> forwardLinks)
      This constructor takes in three parameter which is the currentLink, backLinks, and forwardLinks. Then it sets the links for all three.
      Parameters:
      currentLink - set current link
      backLinks - set back links
      forwardLinks - set forward links

  • Method Details

    • goBack

      public void goBack()
      This constructor warns the user if there is no back links left. If there is back links then it will remove the top link in the back links.

    • goForward

      public void goForward()
      This is similar to the constructor above but the difference is that this one check the forward links.

    • setCurrentLink

      public boolean setCurrentLink​(java.lang.String currentLink)
      This boolean method constructor sets the current link and push previous link to the back links and clear stack forward links. If the currentLink does not have any link then it will return false and nothing will be added. If there is something then the previous currentLink is pushed back.
      Parameters:
      currentLink - link to update
      Returns:
      true or false

    • getForwardLinks

      stack of back links
